imple sample configuration:, +```, +    cloud:, +        azure:, +            keystore: /path/to/keystore, +            password: your_password_for_keystore, +            subscription_id: your_azure_subscription_id, +            service_name: your_azure_cloud_service_name, +    discovery:, +            type: azure, +```, +, +How to start (short story), +--------------------------, +, +* Create Azure instances, +* Install Elasticsearch, +* Install Azure plugin, +* Modify `elasticsearch.yml` file, +* Start Elasticsearch, +, +How to start (long story), +--------------------------, +, +We will expose here one strategy which is to hide our Elasticsearch cluster from outside., +, +With this strategy, only VM behind this same virtual port can talk to each other., +That means that with this mode, you can use elasticsearch unicast discovery to build a cluster., +, +Best, you can use the `elasticsearch-cloud-azure` plugin to let it fetch information about your nodes using, +azure API., +, +### Prerequisites, +, +Before starting, you need to have:, +, +* A [Windows Azure account](http://www.windowsazure.com/), +* SSH keys and certificate]